com.intel.icecp.scheduler.trigger

Class RangeTrigger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.scheduler.trigger.BaseTrigger
      • com.intel.icecp.scheduler.trigger.RangeTrigger

  • public class RangeTrigger
extends BaseTrigger
    Used to schedule a trigger with a Schedule instance.

    Range triggers will pick a random time within a provided time range for the trigger. Range triggers only support scheduling on a daily basis. This means that once the trigger fires at the randomly selected time for the first time, it will fire again 24 hours later.

    If the end time is null for time range, the trigger will be scheduled to fire daily at the exact start time.

    When a trigger fires, a TriggerMessage object is created and published to the publishChannel specified by the trigger.

    Range triggers do not account for daylight saving time. So when creating a range trigger, take into account the selected random time could move an hour forward and/or backward as daylight savings time starts or stops.

      • RangeTrigger

        public RangeTrigger(String id,
                    String startTime,
                    String endTime,
                    String publishChannel,
                    String cmd,
                    Map<String,String> params)
        Constructor
        Parameters:
        id - Unique identifier for the trigger. This unique identifier is used for published trigger event messages to determine the trigger that was fired.
        startTime - Starting time for the range window in local time. The supported TIME_FORMAT is h:mm a.
        endTime - Optional ending time for the range window, in local time. The supported TIME_FORMAT is h:mm a. If endTime is null, the trigger will be set at the startTime value.
        publishChannel - Channel the trigger event should be published on.
